notes: Myxicola sp.A = "Myxicola aff. aesthetica”; In Europe, M. infundibulum is found in soft-sediments and M. aesthetica on docks & hard-surfaces. However, specimens from the NEP are morphologically and genetically different. In the past, several species of Myxicola were described from California, Puget Sound, and Alaska. This material needs to be re-examined.

Myxicola sp.B = "Myxicola aff. infundibulum”; In Europe, M. infundibulum is found in soft-sediments and M. aesthetica on docks & hard-surfaces. However, specimens from the NEP are morphologically and genetically different. In the past, several species of Myxicola were described from California, Puget Sound, and Alaska. This material needs to be re-examined.
